    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a knob of<strong> butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leeks</strong>, <strong>chopped red onion</strong> and <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves] </span></strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until starting to soften, then add the<strong> diced potatoes</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
